column3: Having depends of still officially supported versions point to dead URLs doesn't seem the most advisable, a lot of projects rely on those supported versions being functional in a complete sense\n

> Having depends of still officially supported versions point to dead URLs doesn't seem the most advisable, a lot of projects rely on those supported versions being functional in a complete sense\n\nAh, this change into 0.21 branch.

> `make` terminates as `qt.mk` points to (now) outdated URL path for Qt 5.9 sources, returning error 404

Btw, `make` should use `https://bitcoincore.org/depends-sources` in such cases.
